  "body": "Since this use of recover will also recover other errors, implementation bugs are treated as protocol specified exceptional conditions (e.g. out of gas).\n\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/develop/vm/vm.go#L49\n\nThis affects consensus since e.g. processing of a block will continue in face of running into implementation bugs or a non-valid tx.\n\nWe should clearly separate the VM halting conditions and other exceptions specified in YP from any non-protocol errors / conditions / exceptions.\n\nBlocks / txs in processing should be rejected immediately on an error, and we can consider blacklisting peers advertising such blocks / txs.\n",
